-- Central Bank's Belka Sees No Inflation Risk for Polish Economy, Rp.pl Says
-- Maciej Martewicz
-- 2010-06-15T05:19:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-15/central-bank-s-belka-sees-no-inflation-risk-for-polish-economy-rp-pl-says.html

          
          
             Poland’s economy faces no inflation 
threat in the near future or in the longer term, Marek 
Belka, the country’s central bank governor, told Rp.pl in an 
interview today.  
 The zloty should appreciate due to  “solid” fundamentals,
Belka told the website of Rzeczpospolita newspaper, adding that
he’s “moderately optimistic” about the country’s economic 
outlook.  
